@newsection{5.6,REPORT SECTION}
@diagram{REPORT SECTION,DD-REPORT-SECTION,DD-REPORT-SECTION,None}
@diagram{Report-Description (RD),DD-RS-RD,DD-RS-RD,DD-RS-RD}@p This section describes the layout of printed reports as well as many of the functional aspects of the generation of reports that will be produced via the Report Writer Control System.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{ARE} and @syntax{IS} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item The phrases @syntax{CONTROL IS} and @syntax{CONTROLS ARE} are interchangeable, as are the @syntax{PAGE LIMIT} and @syntax{PAGE LIMITS} phrases.
@p @item The reserved word @syntax{LINES} may be abbreviated as @syntax{LINE}.
@p @item The reserved word @syntax{COLUMNS} may be abbreviated as @syntax{COLS}.
@p @item Each report referenced on a @syntax{REPORT IS} clause (@pxref{File/Sort-Description}) must be described with a report description (@syntax{RD}).
@p @item @xref{GLOBAL}, for information on the @syntax{GLOBAL} option.
@p @item Please see @ref{Report Writer Features}, if you have not read it already.  This will familiarize you with the Report Writer terminology that will follow.
@p @item The following rules pertain to the @syntaxidx{PAGE LIMITS} clause:
@enumerate A
@p @item If no @syntax{PAGE LIMITS} clause is specified, the entire report will be generated as if it consists of a single arbitrarily long page.
@p @item All literals (@term{literal-2} through @term{literal-8}) must be numeric with non-zero positive integer values.
@p @item All identifiers (@term{identifier-2} through @term{identifier-8}) must be numeric, unedited with non-zero positive integer values.
@p @item Any value specified for @term{literal-2}|@term{identifier-2} will define the total number of available lines on any report page, not counting any unused margins at the top and/or bottom of the page (defined by the @syntax{LINES AT TOP} and @syntax{LINES AT BOTTOM} values specified on the @syntax{LINAGE} clause of the @syntax{FD} this @syntax{RD} is linked to --- @pxref{File/Sort-Description}).
@p @item Any value specified for @term{literal-3}|@term{identifier-3} will be ignored.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{HEADING} clause defines the first line number at which a report heading or page heading may be presented.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{FIRST DETAIL} clause defines the first line at which a detail group may be presented.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{LAST CONTROL} HEADING clause defines the last line at which any line of a control heading may be presented.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{LAST DETAIL} clause defines the last line at which any line of a detail group may be presented.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{FOOTING} clause defines the last line at which any line of a control footing group may be presented.
@p @item The following rules establish default values for the various @syntax{PAGE LIMIT} clauses, assuming there is one:
@itemize @bullet
@p @item @syntax{HEADING} --- the default is one (1)
@p @item @syntax{FIRST DETAIL} --- the HEADING value is used
@p @item @syntax{LAST CONTROL HEADING} --- the value from @syntax{LAST DETAIL} or, if that is absent, the value from @syntax{FOOTING} or, if that too is absent, the value from @syntax{PAGE LIMIT}
@p @item @syntax{LAST DETAIL} --- the value from @syntax{FOOTING} or, if that is absent, the value from @syntax{PAGE LIMIT}
@p @item @syntax{FOOTING} --- the value from @syntax{LAST DETAIL} or, if that is absent, the value from @syntax{PAGE LIMIT}
@end itemize
@item For the values specified on a @syntax{PAGE LIMIT} clause to be valid, all of the following must be true:
@itemize @bullet
@p @item @syntax{HEADING} not > @syntax{FIRST DETAIL}
@p @item @syntax{FIRST DETAIL} not > @syntax{LAST CONTROL HEADING}
@p @item @syntax{LAST CONTROL HEADING} not > @syntax{LAST DETAIL}
@p @item @syntax{LAST DETAIL} not > @syntax{FOOTING}
@end itemize
@end enumerate
@item The following rules pertain to the @syntaxidx{CONTROL} clause:
@enumerate A
@p @item If there is no @syntax{CONTROL} clause, the report will contain no control breaks; this implies that there can be no @syntax{CONTROL HEADING} or @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING} report groups defined for this @syntax{RD}.
@p @item Include the reserved word @syntaxidx{FINAL} if you want to include a special control heading before the first detail line is generated (@syntax{CONTROL HEADING FINAL}) or after the last detail line is generated (@syntax{CONTROL FOOTING FINAL}).
@p @item If you specify @syntax{FINAL}, it must be the first control break named in the @syntax{RD}.
@p @item Any @term{identifier-9} specifications included on the @syntax{CONTROL} clause are referencing data names defined in any data division section except for the report section.
@p @item There must be a @syntax{CONTROL HEADING} and/or @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING} report group defined in the report section for each @term{identifier-9}.
@p @item At execution time:
@itemize @bullet
@p @item Each time a @statementref{GENERATE} is executed against a detail report group defined for this @syntax{RD}, the RWCS will check the contents of each @term{identifier-2} data item; whenever an @term{identifier-9}'s value has changed since the previous GENERATE, a control break condition will be in effect for that @term{identifier-2}.
@p @item Once the list of control breaks has been determined, the @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING} for each @term{identifier-2} having a control break (if any such report group is defined) will be presented.
@p @item Next, the @syntax{CONTROL HEADING} for each @term{identifier-2} having a control break (if any such report group is defined) will be presented.
@p @item The @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING} and @syntax{CONTROL HEADING} report groups will be presented in the sequence in which they are listed on the @syntax{CONTROL} clause.
@p @item Only after this processing has occurred will the detail report group specified on the @syntax{GENERATE} be presented.
@end itemize
@end enumerate
@item Each @syntax{RD} will have the following allocated for it:
@enumerate A
@p @item The @registerref{PAGE-COUNTER}, which will contain the current report page number.
@itemize @bullet
@p @item This register will be set to a value of 1 when an @statementref{INITIATE} is executed for the report and will be incremented by 1 each time the RWCS starts a new page of the report.
@p @item References to @syntax{PAGE-COUNTER} within the report section will be implicitly qualified with the name of the report to which the report group referencing the register belongs.
@p @item References to @syntax{PAGE-COUNTER} in the procedure division must be qualified with the appropriate report name if there are multiple @syntax{RD}s defined.
@end itemize
@item The @register{LINE-COUNTER}, which will contain the current line number on the current page.
@end enumerate
@item The @syntax{RD} must be followed by at least one 01-level report group definition.
@end enumerate
@menu
* 5.6.1: Report Group Definitions.
* 5.6.2: REPORT SECTION Data Items.
@end menu
