@p @item The @syntax{RH} and @syntax{REPORT HEADING} terms are interchangeable, as are @syntax{PH} and @syntax{PAGE HEADING}, @syntax{CH} and @syntax{CONTROL HEADING}, @syntax{DE} and @syntax{DETAIL}, @syntax{CF} and @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING}, @syntax{PF} and @syntax{PAGE FOOTING} as well as @syntax{RF} and @syntax{REPORT FOOTING}.
@p @item The report group being defined will be a part of the most-recently coded @syntax{RD}.
@p @item The @syntaxref{TYPE} clause specifies the type of report group being defined.
@p @item The level number used for a report group definition must be 01.
@p @item The optional @term{identifier-1} specification assigns a name to this report group so that the group may be referenced either by a GENERATE statement or on a @syntax{USE BEFORE REPORTING}.
@p @item No two report groups in the same report (@syntax{RD}) may named with the same @term{identifier-1}.  There may, however, be multiple @term{identifier-1} definitions in different reports.  In such instances, references to @term{identifier-1} must be qualified by the report name.
@p @item There may only be one report heading, report footing, final control heading, final control footing, page heading and page footing defined per report.
@p @item Report group declarations must be followed by at least one @clause{REPORT-SECTION-Data-Item} with a level number in the range 02-49.
