@comment ** 5.8.5 88-Level Data Items                                       **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsubsection{5.8.5,88-Level Data Items}@idx{Condition Names}
@diagram{88-Level-Data-Item,DD-88-Data-Item,DD-88-Data-Item,None}
@center This syntax is valid in the following sections:
@center @strong{FILE}, @strong{WORKING-STORAGE}, @strong{LOCAL-STORAGE}, @strong{LINKAGE}, @strong{REPORT}, @strong{SCREEN}
@p Condition names are Boolean (i.e. TRUE / FALSE) data items that receive their TRUE and FALSE values based upon the values of the non 88-level data item whose definition they immediately follow.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{ARE}, @syntax{IS}, @syntax{SET} and @syntax{TO} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{THRU} and @syntax{THROUGH} are interchangeable.
@p @item Condition names are always defined subordinate to another (non 88-level) data item.  That data item must be an elementary item.  Whenever the parent data item assumes one of the values specified on the 88-level item's @syntaxref{VALUE} clause, @term{condition-name-1} will take on the value of TRUE.
@p @item Condition names do not occupy any storage.
@p @item The optional @syntax{THROUGH} clause allows a range of possible TRUE values to be specified.
@p @item Whenever the parent data item assumes any value @i{except} one of the values specified on @term{condition-name-1}'s @syntax{VALUE} clause, @term{condition-name-1} will take on the value of FALSE.
@p @item Executing the statement @syntax{SET @term{condition-name-1} TO TRUE} will cause @term{condition-name-1}'s parent data item to take on the first value specified on @term{condition-name-1}'s @syntax{VALUE} clause.
@p @item Executing the statement @syntax{SET @term{condition-name-1} TO FALSE} will cause @term{condition-name-1}'s parent data item to take on the value specified on @term{condition-name-1}'s @syntax{FALSE} clause.  If @term{condition-name-1} does not have a @syntax{FALSE} clause, the @syntaxref{SET} statement will generate an error message at compilation time.
@p @item @xref{Condition Names}, for more information.
@end enumerate
