@comment ** 5.9.12 COLUMN                                                   **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsubsection{5.9.12,COLUMN}
@diagram{COLUMN (REPORT SECTION) Clause,DD-COLUMN-1,DD-COLUMN-1,None}
@diagram{COLUMN (SCREEN SECTION) Clause,DD-COLUMN-2,DD-COLUMN-2,None}
@center This syntax is valid in the following sections:
@center @strong{REPORT}, @strong{SCREEN}
@p The @syntax{COLUMN} clause provides the means of stating in which column a field should be presented on the console window (screen section) or a report (report section).
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{ARE}, @syntax{IS}, @syntax{NUMBER} and @syntax{NUMBERS} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item The reserved word @syntax{COLUMN} may be abbreviated as @syntax{COL}.
@p @item The line location of a report section or screen section field will be determined by the @syntaxref{LINE} clause.
@p @item The value of @term{integer-1} must be 1 or greater.
@p @item If @term{identifier-1} is used to specify either an absolute or relative column position, @term{identifier-1} must be defined as a numeric item of any @syntaxref{USAGE} other than @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-1} or @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-2}, without editing symbols.  The value of @term{identifier-1} at the time the screen data item is presented must be 1 or greater.  Note that a @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-1} or @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-2} identifier will be accepted by the compiler, but will produce unpredictable results at run-time.
@p @item The column coordinate of a field may be stated on an absolute basis (i.e. @syntax{COLUMN 5}) or on a relative basis based upon the end of the previously-presented field (i.e. @syntax{COLUMN PLUS 1}).
@p @item The symbol @syntax{+} may be used in lieue of the word @syntax{PLUS}, if desired; if symbol @syntax{+} is used, however, there must be at least one space separating it from @term{integer-1}.  Failure to include this space will cause the symbol @syntax{+} sign to be simply treated as part of @term{integer-1} and will treat the @syntax{COLUMN} clause as an absolute column specification rather than a relative one.
@p @item Using relative column positioning (@syntax{COLUMN PLUS}) has slightly different behavior depending upon the section in which the clause is used, as follows:
@enumerate A
@p @item When used on a report section data item, @syntax{COLUMN PLUS} will position the start of the new field's value such that there are @term{integer-1} blank columns between the end of the previous field and the beginning of this field.
@p If a report data item's description includes the @syntaxref{SOURCE}, @syntaxref{SUM} or @syntaxref{VALUE} clause but has no @syntax{COLUMN} clause, @syntax{COLUMN PLUS 1} will be assumed.
@p @item When used on a screen section data item, @syntax{COLUMN PLUS} will position the new field so that it begins exactly @term{integer-1} or @term{identifier-1} characters past the @i{last} character of the previous field.  Thus, @syntax{COLUMN PLUS 1} will  leave no blank positions between the end of the previous field and the start of this one.
@p If a screen data item's description includes the @syntaxref{FROM}, @syntaxref{TO}, @syntaxref{USING} or @syntaxref{VALUE} clause but has no @syntax{COLUMN} clause, the new screen field will begin at the column coordinate of the last character of the previous field.
@end enumerate
