@center This syntax is valid in the following sections:
@center @strong{REPORT}, @strong{SCREEN}
@p This clause provides a means of explicitly stating on which line a field should be presented on the console window (screen section) or on a report (report section).
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{IS}, @syntax{NUMBER} and @syntax{ON} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item The following points document the use of format 1 of the @syntax{LINE} clause:
@enumerate A
@p @item The column location of a report item will be determined by the @syntaxref{COLUMN} clause.
@p @item The value of @term{integer-1} must be 1 or greater.
@p @item The report line number upon which the data item containing this clause along with any subordinate data items will be presented may be stated on an absolute basis (i.e. @syntax{LINE 5}) or on a relative basis based upon the previously-displayed line (i.e. @syntax{LINE PLUS 1}).
@p @item The symbol @syntax{+} may be used in lieue of the word @syntax{PLUS}, if desired; if @syntax{+} is used, however, there must be at least one space separating it from @term{integer-1}.  Failure to include this space will cause the @syntax{+} to be simply treated as part of @term{integer-1} and will treat the LINE clause as an absolute line specification rather than a relative one.
@p @item The optional @syntaxidx{NEXT PAGE} clause specifies that --- regardless of whether or not the report group containing this clause @i{could} fit on the report page being currently generated, the report group will be @i{forced} to appear on a new page.
@end enumerate
@item The following points document the use for format 2 of the @syntax{LINE} clause:
@enumerate A
@p @item The column location of a screen section field is determined by the @syntaxref{COLUMN} clause.
@p @item The value of @term{integer-1} must be 1 or greater.
@p @item If @term{identifier-1} is used to specify either an absolute or relative column position, @term{identifier-1} must be defined as a numeric item of any @syntaxref{USAGE} other than @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-1} or @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-2}, without editing symbols.  The value of @term{identifier-1} at the time the screen data item is presented must be 1 or greater.  Note that a @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-1} or @syntax{COMPUTATIONAL-2} identifier will be accepted by the compiler, but will produce unpredictable results at run-time.
@p @item The screen line number upon which the data item containing this clause along with any subordinate data items will be displayed may be stated on an absolute basis (i.e. @syntax{LINE 5}) or on a relative basis based upon the previously-displayed line (i.e. @syntax{LINE PLUS 1}).
@p @item The symbol @syntax{+} may be used in lieue of the word @syntax{PLUS}, if desired; if @syntax{+} is used, however, there must be at least one space separating it from @term{integer-1}.  Failure to include this space will cause the @syntax{+} to be simply treated as part of @term{integer-1} and will treat the @syntax{LINE} clause as an absolute line specification rather than a relative one.
@p @item If a screen data item's description includes the @syntaxref{FROM}, @syntaxref{TO}, @syntaxref{USING} or @syntaxref{VALUE} clause but has no LINE clause, the "current screen line" will be assumed.
@end enumerate
@end enumerate
