@comment ** 5.9.42 SOURCE                                                   **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsubsection{5.9.42,SOURCE}
@diagram{SOURCE Clause,DD-SOURCE,DD-SOURCE,None}
@center This syntax is valid in the following sections:
@center @strong{REPORT}
@p This clause logically attaches a report section data item to another data item defined elsewhere in the data division.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved word @syntax{IS} is optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of this word has no effect upon the program.
@p @item When the report group containing this clause is presented, the value of the specified numeric literal or identifier will be automatically moved to the report data item prior to presentation.
@p @item The specified identifier may be defined anywhere in the data division, but if it is defined in the report section it may only be @syntaxidx{PAGE-COUNTER}, @syntaxidx{LINE-COUNTER} or a @syntaxref{SUM} counter.
@p @item The @syntaxref{PICTURE} of the report data item must be such that it would be legal to @syntaxref{MOVE} the specified literal or identifier to a data item with that @syntax{PICTURE}.
@p @item The @syntax{ROUNDED} option comes into play should the number of digits to the right of an actual or assumed decimal point be different between the specified literal or identifier value (the "source value") and the @syntax{PICTURE} specified for the field in whose definition the @syntax{SOURCE} clause appears (the "target field").  @i{Without} @syntax{ROUNDED}, excess digits in the source value will simply be truncated to fit the target field.  @i{With} @syntax{ROUNDED}, the source value will be arithmetically rounded to fit the target field.  @xref{ROUNDED}, for information on the @syntax{NEAREST-AWAY-FROM-ZERO} rounding rule, which is the one that will apply.
@end enumerate
@comment *********************************************************************
@comment ** 5.9.43 SUM OF                                                   **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsubsection{5.9.43,SUM OF}
@diagram{SUM-OF Clause,DD-SUM-OF-Info,DD-SUM-OF-TeX,None}
@center This syntax is valid in the following sections:
@center @strong{REPORT}
@p The @syntax{SUM} clause establishes a summation counter whose value will be arithmetically calculated whenever the field is presented.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{OF} and @syntax{ON} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item The @syntax{SUM} clause may only appear in a @syntax{CONTROL FOOTING} report group.
@p @item If the data item in which the @syntax{SUM} clause appears has been assigned it's own identifier name, and that name is not @syntax{FILLER}, then that data item is referred to as a sum counter.
@p @item All @term{identifier-7} data items must be non-edited numeric in nature.
@p @item If any @term{identifier-7} data item is defined in the report section, it must be a sum counter.
@p @item Any @term{identifier-7} data items that are sum counters must either be defined in the same report group as the data item in which this @syntax{SUM} clause appears or they must be defined in a report data item that exists at a lower level in this report's control hierarchy.  @xref{Control Hierarchy}, for additional information.
@p @item The @syntax{PICTURE} of the report data item in who's description this @syntax{SUM} clause appears in must be such that it would be legal to @syntaxref{MOVE} the specified @term{identifier-7} or @term{literal-2} value to a data item with that @syntax{PICTURE}.
@p @item The following points apply to the @syntaxidx{UPON} option:
@enumerate A
@p @item The data item @term{identifier-9} must be the name of a detail group specified in the same report as the control footing group in which this @syntax{SUM} clause appears.
@p @item The presence of an @syntax{UPON} clause limits the @syntax{SUM} clause to adding the specified numeric literal or identifier value into the sum counter only when a @syntax{GENERATE @term{identifier-9}} statement is executed.
@p @item If there is no @syntax{UPON} clause specified, the value of @term{identifier-7} or @term{literal-2} will be added into the sum counter whenever a @syntaxref{GENERATE} of any detail report group in the report is executed.
@p @item If there is only a single detail group in the report's definition, the @syntax{UPON} clause is meaningless.
@end enumerate
@item The following points apply to the @syntaxidx{RESET} option:
@enumerate A
@p @item If the @syntax{RESET} option is coded, @syntax{FINAL} or @term{identifier-8} (whichever is coded on the @syntax{RESET}) must be one of the report's control breaks specified on the @syntax{CONTROLS} clause.
@p @item If there is no @syntax{RESET} option coded, the sum counter will be reset back to zero after each time the control footing containing the @syntax{SUM} clause is presented.  This is the typical behavior that would be expected.
@p @item If, however, you want to reset the @syntax{SUM} counter only when the control footing for a control break higher in the control hierarchy is presented, specify that higher control break on the @syntax{RESET} option.
@end enumerate
@end enumerate
